HEADWORD: Piperine
<hw>Pip"er*ine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>piper</ets> pepper: cf. F. <ets>piperin</ets>,
<ets>piperine</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A white crystalline
compound of piperidine and piperic acid. It is obtained from the black
pepper (<spn>Piper nigrum</spn>) and other species.</def>⟦br⟧
